orbitSensitivity.title: Orbit Sensitivity
orbitSensitivity.description: How fast the camera moves around the orbit. Higher is faster

distanceSensitivity.title: Distance Sensitivity
distanceSensitivity.description: How fast the camera moves in and out. Higher is faster

distanceMax.title: Distance Max
distanceMax.description: Setting this at 0 will give an infinite distance limit

focusEntity.title: Focus Entity
focusEntity.description: Entity for the camera to focus on. If blank, then the camera will use the whole scene

frameOnStart.title: Frame on Start
frameOnStart.description: Frames the entity or scene at the start of the application."

inertiaFactor.title: Inertia Factor
inertiaFactor.description: Higher value means that the camera will continue moving after the user has stopped dragging. 0 is fully responsive.

autoRender.title: Auto Render
autoRender.description: Disable to only render when camera is moving (saves power when the camera is still)

distanceInit.title: Distance Init
distanceInit.description: カメラとオブジェクトの距離の初期値です

orbitSensitivity.title: Orbit Sensitivity
orbitSensitivity.description: How fast the camera moves around the orbit. Higher is faster

distanceSensitivity.title: Distance Sensitivity
distanceSensitivity.description: How fast the camera moves in and out. Higher is faster

camera.title: Camera (Optional)
camera.description:
The camera object to apply bloom effect to. If no camera is provided the script tries
    to use camera component on its current entity. Eventually if no camera is found there as well -
    the first camera in pc.app.systems.camera.cameras is used.

blendmode.title: Blend Mode
blendmode.description:
Bloom blending mode. [Add] is using standard additive mixing, [Screen] results in higher
    contrast in extreme cases like super bright lights, maxed out iterations and low mip limit.

iterations.title: Iterations
iterations.description:
Richness of bloom effect. The difference between 1 and 12 in terms of performance is
    truly negligible so it's recommended to leave it at maximum unless you're targeting specific artistic
    look. Not all iterations may be used internally since downscaling stops at Mip Limit resolution. Low
    and medium number of iterations may produce different results on retina and non-retina displays
    (pc.app.graphicsDevice.maxPixelRatio = 2 or 1), especially with non-zero filter radius.

strength.title: Strength
strength.description: Blending factor. High values together with bright lights result in a steam room look! :D

miplimit.title: Mip Limit
miplimit.description:
This parameter controls the depth of the mip chain by limiting the lowest resolution
    allowed during downscaling. Going below 4 with maxed out iterations may result in a beautiful full
    screen glow which is possible only at sufficiently high resolutions (1024 and up at pixel ratio 1).

thresholdA.title: Threshold A
thresholdA.description:
Thresholding function lower limit. Pixels dimmer than A do not contribute to bloom,
    pixels brighter than B contribute fully, pixels in (A, B) range contribute with smoothstep curve.

thresholdB.title: Threshold B
thresholdB.description:
Thresholding function upper limit. Pixels dimmer than A do not contribute to bloom,
    pixels brighter than B contribute fully, pixels in (A, B) range contribute with smoothstep curve.

radius.title: Filter Radius
radius.description:
Radius of additional blur applied during upsampling stage. It's mostly used to
    dilute a minor moire artefact that is visible at radius (0, 0). Due to the nature of texture
    filtering Filter Radius may produce slightly different bloom kernel depending on device pixel
    ratio (i.e. retina and non-retina displays), so you may want to adjust it dynamically depending
    on window.devicePixelRatio or pc.app.graphicsDevice.maxPixelRatio.

hdrformat.title: HDR Format
hdrformat.description:
Preferred HDR format. Actual format chosen by system may differ due to hardware
    compatibility. 11 bit is the best choice overall, it provides tangible performance benefits and
    is also widely supported even on old devices like iPhone 8. If selected format is not supported
    by target system the first valid lower format will be used.
